{{swp|ja:}}
[[File:Hina arare.jpg|thumb|{{lang|ja|'''あられ''', あられもち}}]]

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=あられ|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|sort=あられ|*arare}}.
Attested from the 8th century. From {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*arare}}. In ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' (a. 759)  {{ja-r|霰|あられ}} appears to refer either to small bits of hail or graupel, or to larger hailstones (contemporary {{ja-r|雹|ひょう}}).<ref>{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Compare dialectal {{m|ja|霰|tr=arane}}, {{cog|mvi|霰|tr=arari}}, {{cog|rys|霰|tr=arari}}.

